<i>the last place anybody
would wanna be.</i>

48:59.063 --> 49:02.157
When Jack gets back,
I'm telling him I protected this island.

49:02.233 --> 49:07.136
We can take 'em, Selk. We have no choice.

49:12.110 --> 49:14.203
No fire tonight, guys.

49:14.278 --> 49:16.610
No fire and no light.

49:16.681 --> 49:18.672
Nobody can know
that we're here.

49:22.887 --> 49:26.152
Come on, guys.
Nobody's out there.

49:26.224 --> 49:29.022
We'll just all close our eyes.

49:40.438 --> 49:43.032
Oh, please.
Please don't take me now.

49:43.107 --> 49:47.203
I promise that if I survive this,
I will never leave the house again.

49:47.278 --> 49:51.044
I promise I will only listen
to my deepest fears and doubts.

49:54.685 --> 49:59.213
<i>Orion is there,
and-and this is April.</i>

49:59.290 --> 50:03.659
Then I must be
nine degrees north of-

50:03.728 --> 50:07.186
There's a shipping lane through-

50:07.265 --> 50:09.233
What?
Am I too far north?

50:11.402 --> 50:13.370
Yeah, maybe you're right.

50:13.437 --> 50:15.701
I mean, you know
your stars, Galileo.

50:26.817 --> 50:28.751
Emily?

50:30.321 --> 50:32.255
Is it you?

50:35.059 --> 50:38.927
I will get back to her, Emily!
I- I swear it!

50:38.996 --> 50:41.658
I will take care of Nim!

50:46.837 --> 50:48.771
Emily?

50:57.348 --> 51:02.217
<i>Look at 'em. I promised Jack
no one gets on our sand.</i>

51:02.286 --> 51:04.686
Courage is something
you find every day.

51:05.790 --> 51:07.724
Selkie, wake up!

51:07.792 --> 51:11.057
<i>Today's the day we fight
for our piece of the world.</i>

51:11.128 --> 51:13.824
<i>This is our island!</i>

51:13.898 --> 51:17.800
Oh, it's fantastic.
Amazing!

51:17.868 --> 51:20.098
<i>Check it out, Dad.
Totally undiscovered.</i>

51:20.171 --> 51:23.470
<i>Course it's discovered, Edmund.
Cruise line done discovered it.</i>

51:23.541 --> 51:25.566
- Come on, Eddie.
- Wait, Mum.

51:25.643 --> 51:28.578
My dollar's not up yet.
Let me take one more squiz.

51:28.646 --> 51:30.580
<i>What the-</i>

51:30.648 --> 51:33.446
Quick, Mum!
Give me another dollar!

51:33.517 --> 51:35.781
- I think I saw a mermaid!
- Come on, Edmund.

51:35.853 --> 51:38.344
Now, move it!
The tender is leaving!

51:38.422 --> 51:41.619
- But the mermaid!
- Come on. Zip it! Here's your hat.

51:41.692 --> 51:44.627
Honey bunny, come on!
It's leaving.

51:48.099 --> 51:50.090
Uh, no, no, no.

51:50.167 --> 51:53.159
I'm- I'm looking for, uh, Fire Mountain.
Uh, there's a volcano there.

51:53.237 --> 51:56.229
Two hamburger. Two hamburger.
Two hamburgers.

51:56.307 --> 51:58.969
- Oh, no, no. That's not a hamburger. Trust me.
- One dollar.

51:59.043 --> 52:01.511
- Oh, you look beautiful.
- One dollar bangle. Very cheap.

52:01.579 --> 52:03.274
Aah.

52:03.347 --> 52:06.180
- Goat. Goat. You need goat.
- No, no, no.

52:06.250 --> 52:08.878
I-I-I don't need a goat.
You-You need that goat.

52:08.953 --> 52:11.854
<i>You should wash your hands
before you touch anything else.</i>

52:11.922 --> 52:15.824
- Buy from me! Buy from me!
- I can't. I need Fire Mountain.

52:15.893 --> 52:18.225
- I know what you need. I take you.
- You know Fire Mountain?

52:18.296 --> 52:21.788
It's 20 degrees south
and 162 degrees west.

52:21.866 --> 52:24.198
- I know what you need. I take you.
- Okay. Um-

52:24.268 --> 52:26.259
- I know.
- All right. I'll get in.

52:26.337 --> 52:29.238
- Toothbrush. Your very own toothbrush!
- I don't need any toothbrushes.

52:29.307 --> 52:31.366
I always bring my own.
Thank you.

52:31.442 --> 52:34.707
You can use that for yourself.
Your own teeth. Brush, brush.

52:34.779 --> 52:37.339
Okay. Thank you.
Good-bye.

52:38.416 --> 52:40.384
<i>Wait! Are you-</i>

52:40.451 --> 52:42.646
Are-Are you positive that
you know where you're going?

52:42.720 --> 52:44.881
I know what you need.
I take you.

52:44.955 --> 52:49.187
You wouldn't happen to have any hand sanitizer
up there amongst all those Coke cans, would you?

52:49.260 --> 52:51.091
I know what you need.
I take you.

52:51.162 --> 52:53.926
That's all you know how to say,
isn't it?

52:53.998 --> 52:56.432
I know what you need.
I take you.

53:00.071 --> 53:02.005
Trust, Alex.

53:02.073 --> 53:04.234
Trust, trust.
That's easy for you to say.

53:04.308 --> 53:07.175
Trust is the secret to adventure.

53:07.244 --> 53:10.839
<i>Chapter four, The Trek to Kilimanjaro.</i>

53:10.915 --> 53:13.349
<i>- Can't you come up with anything more original?
- Boat!</i>

53:13.417 --> 53:16.978
- What you need. Boat!
- Ah. See?

53:17.054 --> 53:20.387
What did I tell you?

53:27.998 --> 53:30.262
<i>They've come to the wrong place.</i>

53:30.334 --> 53:33.030
<i>Nobody invades my island
and gets away with it.</i>

53:33.104 --> 53:35.732
Okay, Selk.
Go get 'em now.

53:35.806 --> 53:40.368
<i>Gas 'em out. Teach 'em what happens when
chunks of dead fish and plantains mix together.</i>

53:45.850 --> 53:48.648
<i>A picture-perfect paradise.</i>

53:48.719 --> 53:51.153
What's that down there?

53:51.222 --> 53:54.385
<i>Some kind of
underwater geyser, maybe.</i>

53:57.561 --> 54:01.258
Oh, my God. What's that filthy smell?

54:04.668 --> 54:07.967
Rancid! Oh!

54:08.038 --> 54:12.236
<i>- Turn this boat around.
- It's horrible! I'm going to vomit.</i>

54:13.644 --> 54:15.942
Hey, look! It's a sea lion.

54:16.013 --> 54:19.278
Look at him. Our very own welcoming committee.

54:19.350 --> 54:21.147
<i>Smells fresher over here.</i>

54:21.218 --> 54:23.880
You gave it your best, Selk.

54:23.954 --> 54:25.922
Jack, where are you?

54:46.510 --> 54:49.343
Keep your eyes
on the horizon.

54:49.413 --> 54:53.509
Keep your eyes on the horizon,
eyes on the horizon. Then you won't vomit.

54:53.584 --> 54:56.553
Eyes on the horizon. Eyes on the-

55:00.791 --> 55:02.850
I'll take you as far
as Tuvalu Island.

55:02.927 --> 55:05.691
- That is as far as the little boat goes.
- Okay.

55:05.763 --> 55:08.288
But-Wh-What's that?

55:08.365 --> 55:11.163
<i>That? Ah.
That is a monsoon.</i>

55:11.235 --> 55:14.636
<i>You-You mean, like a-
like a monsoon monsoon?</i>

55:14.705 --> 55:17.936
<i>Storm wants to come this way.
The sky won't let it.</i>

55:18.008 --> 55:22.172
- And I trust my sky.
- "I trust my sky."

55:22.246 --> 55:25.113
That's a very good line. You know,
I might steal that. I'm a writer.

55:25.182 --> 55:27.309
No, no. My line. I'm a writer too.

55:27.384 --> 55:30.251
- I use line in my story.
- Yeah?

55:30.321 --> 55:33.552
Well. Okay. That's fine.
It's all yours.

55:38.095 --> 55:41.394
No! Hey!

55:49.640 --> 55:53.940
<i>Mateys and wenches,
Buccaneer Olympics in half an hour!</i>

56:03.487 --> 56:05.751
<i>All right, all right. There you go.</i>

56:05.823 --> 56:09.190
What are those little houses
they brought with them?

56:09.260 --> 56:11.421
<i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

56:11.495 --> 56:15.363
<i>the porta-potties are
now open for business.</i>

56:19.537 --> 56:21.471
Drop the volleyball.

56:21.539 --> 56:23.370
My telly.

56:23.440 --> 56:25.465
<i>Edmund, don't go too far.</i>

56:25.543 --> 56:28.068
<i>You don't know what sort of
horrible creatures are in there.</i>

56:28.145 --> 56:30.238
<i>There are no horrible creatures, Mum.</i>

56:33.350 --> 56:36.945
- Aah.
- Shh, Fred. Not yet.

56:37.021 --> 56:39.216
No one can know
that we're here.

56:46.363 --> 56:51.130
Get it off! Get it off!
Get it off me!

56:51.201 --> 56:54.830
Dragon! I saw a dragon!

56:56.373 --> 56:58.773
Help! Flying dragons!
Help!

56:58.842 --> 57:00.833
<i>- Edmund, where were you?
- Help!</i>

57:00.911 --> 57:02.936
What's wrong with
that boy now, Shirley?

57:03.013 --> 57:06.244
<i>The scavenger hunt in 20 minutes.</i>

57:06.317 --> 57:10.276
<i>Any mateys or wenches who
want to explore the island...</i>

57:10.354 --> 57:12.151
<i>20 minutes.</i>

57:14.224 --> 57:16.249
No, don't worry about me, Fred.
I'm okay.

57:16.327 --> 57:19.387
Time for the second wave.
Call to your friends. Come on now.

57:39.583 --> 57:41.551
Oh!

57:45.623 --> 57:48.990
Come on. Move it.
Let me at it, kid.

57:52.229 --> 57:56.165
Okay. Are you ready to really fly, Freddie?

58:11.882 --> 58:14.680
Bury my lollies!
It's on me!

58:14.752 --> 58:17.846
<i>Oh, what is it?</i>

58:17.921 --> 58:21.914
- Shirley, help me! Aah!
- Dragons! Flying dragons!

58:35.839 --> 58:37.898
Dragons!

58:45.182 --> 58:49.414
<i>Oh, they're just lizards, ladies and gentlemen!</i>

58:49.486 --> 58:51.181
They roam all over
these islands.

58:51.255 --> 58:53.348
But, uh, how many lizards
can fly, Captain?

59:10.607 --> 59:14.065
To the boats now.
Come on. Be gone with you.

59:14.144 --> 59:17.944
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, do not fear!
Lizards are afraid of fire!</i>

59:18.015 --> 59:23.043
It's just nature,
and we know how to tame it!

59:23.120 --> 59:27.955
<i>Everyone, please! I'd like to introduce
the world-famous Buccaneer Dancers!</i>

59:55.385 --> 59:58.684
Tuvalu Island.
You walk from here.

59:58.756 --> 01:00:01.190
What? I-I walk?

01:00:01.258 --> 01:00:04.694
Uh, it's-That's like
a hundred yards offshore.

01:00:04.762 --> 01:00:06.923
I mean, you-you said to Tuvalu.

01:00:06.997 --> 01:00:09.261
This is-
This is Tuvalu adjacent.

01:00:09.333 --> 01:00:11.597
<i>Little boat go no farther.
Bad for motor.</i>

01:00:11.668 --> 01:00:15.035
Uh- Uh, you ca-
You can't be serious.

01:00:15.105 --> 01:00:17.198
- Come on. Off you go.
- This is just-

01:00:17.274 --> 01:00:19.936
This is-This is-
This is insanity.

01:00:20.010 --> 01:00:22.706
I know- I know a little
thing about insanity, let me tell ya.

01:00:22.780 --> 01:00:24.714
Oh, God.

01:00:24.782 --> 01:00:27.546
<i>Man with a helicopter live here.
He'll take you the rest of the way.</i>

01:00:27.618 --> 01:00:30.086
<i>- But I-
- You find that man with the helicopter.</i>

01:00:30.154 --> 01:00:33.612
Oh, no, no, no. Wait, wait. Don't you know
what the safety ratings are on those things?

01:00:33.690 --> 01:00:36.557
I can't take a helicopter.
I need to go back right now.

01:00:36.627 --> 01:00:38.686
Come on. Right now!

01:00:38.762 --> 01:00:42.391
- Hey! I-I'm reporting you to, uh-
- So long! Good luck!

01:00:42.466 --> 01:00:45.731
<i>someone!</i>

01:00:45.803 --> 01:00:48.067
Now you're up to
your waist in it.

01:00:48.138 --> 01:00:50.368
- The beautiful ocean.
- Ah!

01:00:50.440 --> 01:00:52.931
The salt water.
Doesn't it feel just great?

01:00:53.010 --> 01:00:56.241
No. No. It doesn't feel just-
great.

01:00:56.313 --> 01:00:59.009
It doesn't even feel good.
It feels like the wet, disgusting, fishy and-

01:00:59.082 --> 01:01:03.018
Hey, hey, hey! Hey! Take me back!

01:01:03.086 --> 01:01:05.077
Ach! Away with ya, Alexandra.

01:01:05.155 --> 01:01:08.249
This is it!
You're tasting adventure.

01:01:11.195 --> 01:01:13.720
It tastes bad.

01:01:16.266 --> 01:01:18.530
<i>What's wrong?</i>

01:01:18.602 --> 01:01:21.070
- Have you seen Edmund?
- No.

01:01:21.138 --> 01:01:23.072
Edmund!

01:01:28.912 --> 01:01:31.938
Eddie! Are you in there?

01:01:32.015 --> 01:01:33.983
<i>Play nicely now!</i>

01:01:34.051 --> 01:01:36.110
This is no place for games!

01:01:36.186 --> 01:01:38.711
It's the perfect place
for games!

01:01:38.789 --> 01:01:41.053
Edmund!

01:01:49.266 --> 01:01:52.099
<i>Look up there.</i>

01:01:52.169 --> 01:01:54.729
What's that?

01:01:54.805 --> 01:01:57.774
<i>Yes! Smoke!</i>

01:01:57.841 --> 01:02:00.867
Act like a volcano!

01:02:12.155 --> 01:02:15.283
What is it?
Is it erupting?

01:02:26.703 --> 01:02:28.967
Is that an avalanche?

01:02:39.583 --> 01:02:42.882
Come on.

01:02:44.054 --> 01:02:46.522
No. No. Wrong way!

01:02:49.860 --> 01:02:51.794
Wow.

01:02:53.897 --> 01:02:57.628
Shirley? Shirley!

01:02:57.701 --> 01:02:59.760
Oh.

01:03:11.515 --> 01:03:13.983
Whoa. Did I do that?

01:03:17.688 --> 01:03:19.952
- Geez!
- Edmund!

01:03:21.692 --> 01:03:25.355
<i>Off we go! Don't panic.</i>

01:03:25.429 --> 01:03:28.728
It's part of the experience.
Back onto the boats.

01:03:28.799 --> 01:03:30.733
<i>- Edmund, hurry up!
- Let's move!</i>

01:03:30.801 --> 01:03:33.065
The-The thing's going!
Hurry up!

01:03:46.783 --> 01:03:48.774
<i>Who are you?</i>

01:03:50.387 --> 01:03:52.981
What were you
doing up there?

01:03:54.458 --> 01:03:57.825
- Do you live here?
- Yes, I live here.

01:03:57.894 --> 01:04:00.385
What are you doing here?

01:04:00.464 --> 01:04:03.433
We're supposed to be on holiday.

01:04:03.500 --> 01:04:05.764
Calm down!
Ludwig, get on the boat.

01:04:05.836 --> 01:04:08.737
<i>Get us out of here.</i>

01:04:08.805 --> 01:04:11.103
<i>- Hurry!
- Shirley!</i>

01:04:11.174 --> 01:04:14.371
- Come on! Where's our boy? Get the boy!
- I don't know! Edmund!

01:04:14.444 --> 01:04:16.878
Edmund, now!

01:04:18.281 --> 01:04:21.250
You're different
than I imagined you.

01:04:22.486 --> 01:04:25.250
You-You imagined me?

01:04:25.322 --> 01:04:28.758
<i>From the story,
Buccaneer Ship?</i>

01:04:28.825 --> 01:04:31.419
"The Oceanographer
and the Blue Whale."

01:04:31.495 --> 01:04:33.486
But I'm not from a story.

01:04:41.838 --> 01:04:44.568
<i>Edmund! Hurry up!</i>

01:04:44.641 --> 01:04:46.472
I'm from Brisbane.

01:04:46.543 --> 01:04:48.477
- Edmund!
- Edmund!

01:04:48.545 --> 01:04:51.946
<i>- Ladies and gentlemen, do not panic.
- Edmund!</i>

01:04:52.015 --> 01:04:54.745
Edmund!

01:04:54.818 --> 01:04:57.218
<i>Edmund! Hurry!</i>

01:04:57.287 --> 01:05:00.654
- It's time for you to leave now.
- Are you coming with us?

01:05:00.724 --> 01:05:04.319
- Why?
- It's not safe here.

01:05:04.394 --> 01:05:07.830
- But it's safe for me.
- But you're all alone.

01:05:09.699 --> 01:05:12.429
<i>Hurry up!</i>

01:05:12.502 --> 01:05:14.902
<i>Edmund!</i>

01:05:14.971 --> 01:05:17.235
Coming, Mother.

01:05:21.645 --> 01:05:24.808
<i>Edmund! Eddie?</i>

01:05:24.881 --> 01:05:27.782
Eddie, baby,
where have you been?

01:05:27.851 --> 01:05:30.183
We've been looking for you everywhere.
We've gotta get out of here.

01:05:30.253 --> 01:05:32.687
I met a girl!
Mum, I met a girl!

01:05:32.756 --> 01:05:36.021
Met a girl on this godforsaken island?
I'm happy for you.

01:05:36.093 --> 01:05:39.620
- A girl who lives here.
- Oh, you and your stories, Eddie!

01:05:39.696 --> 01:05:42.529
This island is no place for human beings.
I promise you that.

01:05:42.599 --> 01:05:44.760
Now, come on.
Wait for us! Please!

01:05:44.835 --> 01:05:47.599
<i>- Wait for us!
- We're coming!</i>

01:05:47.671 --> 01:05:49.696
<i>My God! Look at that!</i>

01:05:55.612 --> 01:05:59.013
Move it faster! Come on!

01:05:59.082 --> 01:06:02.984
How old are you now?
Eddie? Eddie?

01:06:03.053 --> 01:06:06.022
No more Game Boy, no more
television for a month.

01:06:06.089 --> 01:06:08.182
He's staying at home
forever.

01:06:15.265 --> 01:06:19.292
Oh, no. Alex Rover, where are you?

01:06:23.773 --> 01:06:26.970
What's happening?

01:06:27.043 --> 01:06:29.136
Storm's changing course!
This is bad!

01:06:29.212 --> 01:06:31.578
- What?
- This is bad!

01:06:31.648 --> 01:06:34.879
Oh! Oh, this is it!
I'm gonna die!

01:06:34.951 --> 01:06:37.977
- I gotta agree with you on that one.
- What?

01:06:38.054 --> 01:06:41.319
Glass bubble hanging a hundred feet
above the middle of nowhere.

01:06:41.391 --> 01:06:45.225
Oh, I hate helicopters.
It's my Achilles' heel.

01:06:45.295 --> 01:06:47.763
You can't say that. You're a hero!

01:06:47.831 --> 01:06:51.494
I'm not a hero. I wish I were.
I'm just a helicopter pilot.

01:06:51.568 --> 01:06:56.096
- Oh!
- No, you're the hero, Alexandra.

01:06:56.173 --> 01:06:58.835
You came all the way down here
just to answer a distress call.

01:06:58.909 --> 01:07:03.369
You-You seized the moment,
claiming control of this part of your life!

01:07:03.446 --> 01:07:06.847
<i>- I'm gonna be sick.
- No, no. No, no, no, no.</i>

01:07:06.917 --> 01:07:09.715
<i>- You can't. Oh!
- What's that?</i>

01:07:12.422 --> 01:07:14.617
I-I think
it's a cruise ship.

01:07:14.691 --> 01:07:18.252
<i>- I'm taking her down. We land there.
- There?</i>

01:07:18.328 --> 01:07:21.525
No!

01:07:28.805 --> 01:07:31.035
South by southeast, full speed.

01:07:31.107 --> 01:07:33.268
Captain, you might
want to see this.

01:07:38.949 --> 01:07:41.247
Good Lord.

01:07:45.689 --> 01:07:49.056
No more!

01:07:49.125 --> 01:07:52.060
No more! No more!

01:07:52.128 --> 01:07:55.393
Oh, thank you!

01:07:57.500 --> 01:08:00.492
Who gave you permission
to land on my ship?

01:08:00.570 --> 01:08:03.471
- Who are you?
- I'm Alex Rover.

01:08:03.540 --> 01:08:05.838
Alex Rover? The adventurer?

01:08:05.909 --> 01:08:09.606
No! The writer!

01:08:12.315 --> 01:08:16.115
Come on now! Don't let me down here!
You're my last chance!

01:08:16.185 --> 01:08:18.450
Come on! Come on!

01:08:18.520 --> 01:08:20.613
That's it!

01:08:20.689 --> 01:08:22.715
Come on!

01:08:22.792 --> 01:08:26.250
You did it!

01:08:26.328 --> 01:08:28.627
<i>Whoo-hoo! Okay. Come on!</i>

01:08:28.698 --> 01:08:33.192
Take me home!
Come on, Mother Nature!

01:08:33.270 --> 01:08:35.261
Take me back to Nim!

01:08:36.606 --> 01:08:38.938
Whoo-hoo!

01:08:39.009 --> 01:08:41.773
I know the coordinates perfectly well.
They're right in my head.

01:08:41.845 --> 01:08:44.904
It is, uh, 20 degrees south,
162 degrees west.

01:08:44.981 --> 01:08:46.971
There's a little girl there.

01:08:47.050 --> 01:08:49.314
There's no girl for 200 miles.

01:08:49.386 --> 01:08:51.718
<i>Oh, but she's-she's
all alone on an island.</i>

01:08:51.787 --> 01:08:54.221
And but-but what-

01:08:54.291 --> 01:08:56.486
Why is everybody looking at me
like I'm crazy?

01:08:56.559 --> 01:09:00.825
